This paper discusses the calculation of bibliometric indicators, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the presence of biases in favor of or against particular fields of science, which could be relevant to the study of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a mathematical framework for calculating percentile-based indicators, which could be of interest to researchers in scientific computing (cs.SI).
